-- Fed Funds Projected to Open at 0.06% to 0.09%, ICAP Says
-- B y   L i z   C a p o   M c C o r m i c k
-- 2012-01-18T11:59:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/fed-funds-projected-to-open-at-0-06-to-0-09-icap-says.html
Fed funds, the U.S. overnight inter-
bank lending  rate , is projected to open from 0.06 percent to
0.09 percent, within the  Federal Reserve ’s target range of zero
to 0.25 percent.  Fed funds closed at 0.28 percent yesterday after trading
from 0.05 percent to 0.28 percent and averaging 0.09 percent,
ICAP Plc, the world’s largest inter-dealer broker, said in an e-
mailed statement. ICAP’s monthly average is 0.07 percent.  The Fed will hold two separate operations involving U.S.
debt today as part of its plan to replace $400 billion of short-
term debt in its portfolio with longer-term Treasuries to reduce
borrowing costs further and counter rising risks of a recession.  Beginning at 10:15 a.m. New York time, the central bank
will sell Treasuries due from November 2013 to February 2014.
The Fed plans to divest $8 billion to $8.75 billion of
securities today, according to the New York Fed’s website. This
operation will close at 11 a.m.  Starting at 1:15 p.m. and ending at 2 p.m., the Fed will
purchase Treasuries maturing from February 2020 to November
2021. The central bank will buy $4.25 billion to $5 billion of
Treasuries in this maturity range.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Liz Capo McCormick in New York at 
